product_name: MACMini MAC Prep + Prime Fix+ Primer and Setting Spray
summary: SummaryMAC Prep + Prime Fix+ Primer and Setting Spray is an alcohol-free, mega-multitasking setting spray that hydrates, primes, refreshes and sets makeup. The fan-favorite setting spray you know and love now comes with a fine-mist pump to adore.
details: DetailsBenefitsProvides an allover hydrating glow to skinInstantly illuminates and adds shimmering radianceHydrates skinPrimes, sets and refreshes makeupMelds makeup into skin for a natural-looking, seamless finishKeeps makeup looking fresh for up to 12 hoursAlcohol-freeDermatologist-testedOphthalmologist-testedDoes not cause acneFeaturesGood-for-skin ingredients, including vitamins and minerals, along with green tea, chamomile and cucumber extractsMultitasking setting sprayHydratesPrimesSetsRefreshesUse this Artist-approved overachiever setting spray in even more innovative ways to power up pigments, erase makeup errors, sheer out foundation, etcFormulated WithoutOilFormaldehydeHydroquinoneTriclosanCoal TarTolueneSodium Laureth SulfateGlutenPhthalateParabenMineral OilPetrolatumPolyethyleneLauryl SulfateOxybenzoneItem 2510727How To UseHold setting spray 12 inches away from face and spray evenly. Use alone or to finish makeup. For face products, apply your favorite powder foundation and lightly mist setting spray all over face to set and hydrate. For color products, apply your favorite Eyeshadow or Pigment to your preferred brush, lightly mist bristles and sweep across lids for an intensified shadow look.IngredientsOriginal: Water\Aqua\Eau, Glycerin, Butylene Glycol, Cucumis Sativus (Cucumber) Fruit Extract, Chamomilla Recutita (Matricaria) Extract, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Tocopheryl Acetate, Caffeine, Panthenol, Arginine, PEG-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, PPG-26-Buteth-26, Fragrance (Parfum), Disodium EDTA, Phenoxyethanol.Please read the ingredient list on the packaging of your product to be sure that the ingredients are appropriate for your personal use.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Hold setting spray 12 inches away from face and spray evenly. Use alone or to finish makeup. For face products, apply your favorite powder foundation and lightly mist setting spray all over face to set and hydrate. For color products, apply your favorite Eyeshadow or Pigment to your preferred brush, lightly mist bristles and sweep across lids for an intensified shadow look.
ingredients: Phenoxyethanol.Please read the ingredient list on the packaging of your product to be sure that the ingredients are appropriate for your personal use

reviews.headline: The best
reviews.comments: I use powder foundation bc I have oily skin especially in the summer. Sets makeup beautifully, not heavy.  The sprayer mist is very fine. Love it.

reviews.headline: Not for an oily girl in Texas
reviews.comments:
Did nothing at all. 
Within two hours, my make up was separated around my nose and mouth. 2 more hours in, I had to completely redo my make up all over. 
It was as if I put nothing on at all.
Thinking this was a fluke, I used half the bottle before making a judgment. 
As a teenager and mostly through my 20s, all I ever used was Mac. 
The milani one is WAY cheaper and actually works. Finally found one worth sticking with.

reviews.headline: Awful!
reviews.comments: This product is awful. The old fix plus was so good. Mac has completely nose dove off a diving board into a shallow end. It doesnt do anthing good. Mist doesnt apray good. You have to use alot in order for it to work. Miss the old packaging and product

reviews.headline: Better than setting powder
reviews.comments: This stuff makes my skin look flawless. I have really sensitive skin and this works so much better than a setting powder.

reviews.headline: Bring back the old bottle
reviews.comments: This was my holy grail up until MAC changed the bottle. The product seems to go everywhere except for on my face, no matter how close/far I get to my face. I'm going through this product quicker than I normally do!

reviews.headline: Great product for summer
reviews.comments: Great product

reviews.headline: Great setting spray
reviews.comments: I love this product! I have used this product for over 12 years and if the protons out off stock I wait. I've used other setting sprays and I am always disappointed.

reviews.headline: hate to love it
reviews.comments: i have tried so many different setting sprays, and this one is simply the best. i use it before and after setting powder to ensure my makeup lasts all day and it DOES. i love a bargain, but this is the one thing i will continue to splurge on.

reviews.headline: Mac changed formula for worse
reviews.comments: Mac changed the formual. No longer works great. Doesnr set make up. Who ever is in charge hasnt done mac justice

reviews.headline: Mac changed formula for worse
reviews.comments: Mac changed the formual. No longer works great. Doesnr set make up. Who ever is in charge hasnt done mac justice

reviews.headline: Received as a Sample
reviews.comments: Works good but doesn't last as long maybe a good 8hrs a tad pricey. Would buy and only use for important occasions.

reviews.headline: LOVE!!!!
reviews.comments: First of all i am immediately buying the full size of this setting spray as soon as i can. Hydrating, priming, and definitely helps lock in the makeup and makes me look sooo fresh and plump. I have acne prone skin so that was my main worry about using this, its been almost two weeks NO active pimples are popping up i am so fricken happy about that !!! I will also say this frangrance yall are smelling….i dont smell it?? i mean yeah it definitely smells like something but its not like extremely fragranced or anything so maybe yall are getting bad batches bc like i said i have acne prone skin so fragranced products are a no for me and i dont really smell it at all which i also love !! i realy recommend if you wear a full base like i do almost daily this spray really helps with cakeyness and refreshing my makeup look. i highly recommend!!!

reviews.headline: Returned!
reviews.comments: I was so wanting to purchase this, I got it and I went to spray it for the 1st time and holy cow the strong, unpleasant fragrance! After that, I really cannot tell you how it held my makeup. MAC , some of us are super sensitive! Remove the fragrance!

reviews.headline: Bring back the old spray bottle!!!
reviews.comments: The new spray nossle on this update version is NOT good. I can barley get any product on my face from the mist. I have to literally hold it rigjt at my face to get anything. And i use so much of the product now because the mist is horrible. The old nossle was SOOOO much better. Actually soaked my face. This new one doesnt get the job done. Will be switching to something else after years of using this one.

reviews.headline: Not the same…
reviews.comments: There was nothing wrong with the old MAC Fix + and I would've continued purchasing it if they hadn't changed anything. The OG was perfect, I would soak my face and let it dry and it would just melt everything together. This new formula feels like it has more alcohol so you can soak your face and it just dries up shortly after (in order to change the bottle for a fine mist, they would have to change the formula, and they did). It's just another setting spray now. Reminds me a lot of the Milani Make it Last setting spray but a lot more expensive. I'll stick with the Elf dewy coconut setting spray for now. I have combo skin and I like a dewy airbrushed look.

reviews.headline: Did not set anything
reviews.comments: I used to use Urban Decay All Nighter and gave this Mac setting spray a try after it was on sale. Not worth a penny in my opinion! Make up did not set, was still moving around over the course of the day and made me look really oily too. I have tried it with several different foundations but that did not make a difference. will definitely go back to UD! The only think I liked was the spray bottle as it really gives a fine subtle mist.

reviews.headline: the best
reviews.comments: this is definitely a holy-grail of mine. i use it to prime, melt my powders, and set everything into place. i haven't found anything comparable, love it

reviews.headline: Fix +
reviews.comments: This product is my holy grail. I use it between almost every step of my base routine! It adds hydration back into the face when makeup becomes dry, and it helps to emulsify products together so you can avoid a powder/cakey look.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I am in LOVE with Fix+. When I first started using MAC products, I tried products based on popularity. Everything I saw that was raved about by MAC, was first on my list. This was the #1 products I heard people talking about. I was skeptical, like so many others, but I tried it and instantly fell in love.

I personally use this to sandwich in my makeup. I moisturize, prime, spray Fix+, apply my makeup, then spray Fix+ again to set it. I have really dry skin, so this is great for adding moisture. Also, it doesn't take much for my makeup to look "cakey". If I spend a little too much time buffing product into my skin, then conceal and powder, it can add up quickly. It doesn't take much product on my skin to really build up. This is great in those cases. Even if you maybe applied a little too much powder, spraying this will take away some of the dryness and buildup.

I also have to rave about the packaging. I've been using it for months now, and every time I've sprayed it, it has been a consistent, light mist. You never have to worry about large drops of the product hitting your skin to create patchy areas. It's always consistent and solid. It also locks for travel, so it won't spill out in your bag.

This is also great for intensifying the color of your eyeshadow and refreshing your skin and makeup throughout the day!
faceoff_positive.headline: Best Versatile Product EVER!

faceoff_negative.comments: I have been using this product on and off for a long time. I spray it on my makeup brush so the full coverage makeup goes on smoother, I also spray it on my face after powder to set. It smells fabulous and it does help your making last longer. I am really disappointed in the new spray head on the bottle. I'm not sure how long ago they made the change since I haven't ordered this in a while. I still have my old bottle and the difference is night and day. My old bottle will lightly mist the product on to your face. The bottle I received last week litteraly streams it out. I can no longer just spray directly on to my face. I have to spray it on my wrist and dab my brush in it to apply. The first time I went to set my makeup my face was dripping wet from one pump and I had to redo that portion of my makeup.
faceoff_negative.headline: Disappointed with the new bottle
